summary: Killing Eve. Season 1. 7.9/10 About Eve, who is obsessed with stopping a really good assassin.  I love this. Trying to create...
caption:
Killing Eve.
Season 1.
7.9/10

About Eve, who is obsessed with stopping a really good assassin. 

I love this. Trying to create change with power you don’t have because the law is dumb. 

Poor Sebastian. 

I love the introduction of Martin, the dog. 

I am so pleased by the whole psychological game that these two play and have with each other. I love how smart they are. I love how psycho they are. I love how much they both learn because of each other. Ugh, the emotions and actions they both show are so good. *claps* 

God, I didn’t like Frank at all. 

Ugh. I wish I had enough self confidence and assurance in my skills to be fully able to take care of myself in any situation. 

Sandra’s acting is A1. God bless. I love her and her character. 

Memorable Quotes:
“If in doubt, don’t go out.”

Summary:

“You dressed up for me,” a very soft voice said.

Bill’s head shot up. Holden fucking Ford was standing in the doorway of the kitchen, with his stupid good boy haircut, a short-sleeved baby blue button down shirt tucked into his dumb trousers. He looked like he had stepped out of a Norman Rockwell painting.

Holden’s smile faded. “Please don’t run,” he said.

–

A Killing Eve AU.

body: i really wanna discuss villanelle and anna’s relationship, i’m new here, but ive seen a few posts being just like “aw look villanelle is gay” about it. but anna was a teacher and villanelle a kid, no matter how manipulative villanelle was. like the scene were they both say she seduced me makes me wonder how “good and nice” anna really was bc despite everything she still had sex w a child mutiple times. and there are other things in the last episode that makes you question anna’s narrative of it all. having a kid in their scenes together makes everything fragile and makes you wonder how old villanelle was. and when the kid asks if villanelle is a pedophile. etc etc
